[2018-08-02 02:27] elyot: Hey guys, apologies for literally not answering anything in like 5 days, I got very sick with food poisoning and have not been able to do much this week
[2018-08-02 02:35] elyot: @Deleted User Reducing cramping is for both functionality and aesthetics. It's hard to click things when there is too much in a row, and it also looks ugly.
@TiboTeebs Yes, we're eventually hoping to do a mobile port, but that depends on a lot of things.
@Miccull Once we go free-to-play, we are expecting hundreds of thousands of new players, and thousands or tens of thousands of concurrents.
@darkeisbein We had a tabletop version, we even had tokens for 3 drones and 10 drones and we would turn them sideways to "tap" them to spend gold. But really tabletop is quite annoying because of no sword and shield numbers. You have to do a lot of bean-counting.
@ruinedshadows We're working on checkpoint-saving for missions. We'll see.
@ruinedshadows Yeah we're looking into the master announcement too. It's supposed to work. It worked in testing... >_<
@jeacaveo (#NeverBrowserer) Customizable unit placement seems like an overkill option. It would be difficult to even have a good interface for people to specify it, and it might make streams less watchable. I mean anything is possible but there needs to be a compelling reason why some people would want it one way and some would want it another way.
@sim "flip board" feature for observers and analysis mode is a feature that's always been on our list but it never seems to be high enough priority. Maybe some day!
[2018-08-02 02:40] elyot: @1m2o That fucking bug has been dogging us for months and I think I finally fucking found the reason this morning. Like, I was literally brushing my teeth, getting ready to go to bed, and it hit me. Turned all the lights back on, went back to the computer, looked at the code, and sure enough, I found something that can cause that problem. It's a very rare bug, basically you need to get automatched on the same FRAME that you load into another game. I still need to very reproduceability though, then I can start to think about a fix. But yes, at long last this fucking thing will be dealt with.
